<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-41-1220 </DOCNO><TEXT>Reviews India's energy resources and compares its coal resources and populationwith those of major coal producing countries. Describes major coalfieldsand the characteristics of the coal and tabulates reserves by depth.Presents the state of exploration of the coal deposits and reviews methodsfor their optimal exploitation. Concludes that in view of its large coalresources and the likely exhaustion of its natural gas resources by theturn of the century, India must develop an energy model incorporatinga greater role for coal in a multi-fuel economy.</TEXT></DOC>